The paper deals with the study of coalgebras, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and logic (cs.LO). The use of the free algebra adjunction and monads is also a topic in category theory (cs.CT). The paper also discusses the application of coalgebras to continuous dcpos and stably continuous frames, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of coalgebras for diagonalization of endomaps is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
